30c7c17f13-09-11 30c7c17fMasters of the Universe Ten sleep  30c7c17f 30c7c17f2nd ascent though more like 3rd since Siegrist did General Litzenheimer. MOTU climbs the crux section of GL to the good rest then steps right to finish up Galactic Emperor. Me: I cannot send Metz Hill. FML.
Joel: Haha you are so much weaker than me when I was 18!
Me: I just sent Metz Hill plus Apollo and Pod. Suggit!
Joel: Nice dude, Hey do you think anyone has ever done the first ascent of Still Life, apollo, mercy, bc, and...just for the hell of it, a 2nd try fa of kill whitey in a day? that would be cool.
Me: (knowing Joel has done this) That would be impressive
Joel: 14a? 13d?
Me: I'm taking 13b to spite you
Joel: I accept that. It is interesting to watch a grown man attempt what was a little boy's plaything so many years ago.
Me: it'll be 13d in the next book, just so the New can say it has a 13d harder than Living in Fear		 ***b9180a5d

b0cc101413-10-18 b0cc1014Travisty New River Gorge  b0cc1014 b0cc10142nd ascent of Harrison Dekker's original method, I think. Sounds stupid and contrived to not use the path of least resistance but this is the way the route was originally intended and the two varying sequences are actually about 6 feet apart. Go right from the horizontal letterbox before the crux. At the big horizontal where you clip the bolt at the lip of the overhang, make a big move left, then a big move up and right to the three finger dish and go straight up through sidepulls. No bailing to the corner. ***b0cc1014

a32ec07312-06-19 a32ec073Crazy Woman Left Crazy Woman Harda32ec073 a32ec07313c/d in book. hard crimpy line. For me, as hard as Galactic or Doomsday.Credited to Alex Catlin 1988.
